ancisco |title = Victimas de la guerra civil |publisher = Temas de Hoy |year= 1999 |location= Madrid |language = es |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |title = The Victorious Counter-revolution: The Nationalist Effort in the Spanish Civil War |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=jSO-dC5ac_EC&pg=PA205 |first=Michael |last=Seidman |publisher = University of Wisconsin Press |year=2011 |isbn = 978-0-299-24964-9}}\n* {{cite book |last= Stoff |first = Laurie |title = Spain |publisher = Greenhaven Press |location = San Diego, CA |year = 2004 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Taylor |first = F. Jay |author-link = F. Jay Taylor |orig-year = 1956 |year = 1971 |title = The United States and the Spanish Civil War, 1936\u20131939 |publisher=Bookman Associates |location = New York, NY |isbn = 978-0-374-97849-5 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Thomas |first = Hugh |author-link = Hugh Thomas (historian) |orig-year=1961, 1987, 2001 |year = 2003 |title = The Spanish Civil War |publisher = Penguin |location = London, England|isbn = 0-14-101161-0 |oclc = 248799351 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Werstein |first=Irving |title = The Cruel Years: The Story of the Spanish Civil War |publisher = Julian Messner |location = New York, NY |year= 1969 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Westwell |first = Ian |title = Condor Legion: The Wehrmacht's Training Ground |publisher= Ian Allan |year = 2004 |ref = harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Brou\u00e8 |first=Pierre |year= 1988 |title= The Revolution and the Civil War in Spain |publisher = Haymarket |location=Chicago, IL |oclc= 1931859515}}\n* {{cite book |last= Carr |first=Sir Raymond |origyear=1977 |title= The Spanish Tragedy: The Civil War in Perspective |publisher=Phoenix Press |year = 2001 |isbn=1-84212-203-7}}\n* De Meneses, Filipe Ribeiro [https://www.questia.com/library/107523308/franco-and-the-spanish-civil-war Franco and the Spanish Civil War], Routledge, London, 2001\n* {{cite book |