o Pasar\u00e1n! Speech]] Dolores Ib\u00e1rruri's famous rousing address for the defense of the Second Republic\n* [http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/services/library/mrc/explorefurther/digital/scw \"Trabajadores: The Spanish Civil War through the eyes of organised labour\"], a digitised collection of more than 13,000 pages of documents from the archives of the British [[Trades Union Congress]] held in the [[Modern Records Centre, University of Warwick]]\n* {{cite book | first = Ronald | last = Hilton | url = http://historicaltexta36rchive.com/books.php?op=viewbook&bookid=11 | title = Spain, 1931\u201336, From Monarchy to Civil War, An Eyewitness Account | publisher = Historical text A36rchive | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160406132323/http://historicaltexta36rchive.com/books.php?op=viewbook&bookid=11 | archive-date = 6 April 2016 | df = dmy-all}}.\n* {{cite web | url = https://www.marxists.org/history/spain/writers/low-brea/red_spanish_notebook.html | first1 = Mary | last1 = Low | first2 = Juan | last2 = Bre\u00e1 | title = Red Spanish Book | publisher = Benjamin Peret}}. A testimony by two surrealists and trotskytes\n* {{cite book | last = Lunn | first = Arnold | title = Spanish Rehearsal | year = 1937}}.\n* {{cite book | last = Peers | first = Allison | title = The Spanish Tragedy | year = 1936}}.\n* {{cite web | url = http://www.weisbord.org/ | title = A collection of essays | first1 = Albert | first2 = Vera | last1 = Weisbord | last2 = Weisbord}} with about a dozen essays written during and about the Spanish Civil War.\n* {{cite web | title = Magazines and journals published during the war | type = online exhibit | publisher = The [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]] | url = http://magazinesandwar.com/}}.\n* {{cite web | title = Revistas y guerra | url = http://www.revistasyguerra.com/ | language = Spanish |trans-title=Magazines & war | publisher = The University of Illinois | place = Urbana\u2010Champaign}}.\n* {{cite 